# Media (Audio & Video)

### Connect with media
```javascript
await ZYNQ.peer.connect(peerId, {
  video: true,
  audio: true,
  resolution: 720,   // or 1080
  fps: 30
})
```

### Handle streams
```javascript
// Local stream (your camera/mic)
ZYNQ.peer.on('local-stream', stream => {
  localVideo.srcObject = stream
})

// Remote stream
ZYNQ.peer.on('remote-stream', ({ peerId, stream }) => {
  remoteVideo.srcObject = stream
})
```

### Stream Management
- Streams are cached per exact configuration (video+audio+resolution+fps)
- Reference counting prevents unnecessary `getUserMedia` calls
- Streams are automatically reused across multiple sessions
- Clean release when no longer needed
